		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Personally i would gladly give up my mana pool in order to do an incredible amount of damage in an emergency situation. Most wizards i talk to always have the same story of dieing in a raid wipe with over half their mana left(due to FT,mind buffs,etc) when a well placed MB, that wasnt an absoulute insult to our class, could have helped turn the tide. I have read just about every post in this thread and i am entirely against the options presented by the company. The members of the wizard community have put up excellent advice but in the tradition that we know, it will be ignored in order to make "everyone" happy. Gradually over the past expansions our class is getting behind in role of DPS, yes we do excellent burst dps but that diminishes further with the higher resists. An unresistable MB is the way to go in that regard. <br><br>SKs and Necros are always increasing in dmg in their insta-hit abilities. Why keep us behind the curve? Why make us only equal of that? We are pure and simple DPS and we live on that alone. To keep us under them makes our agreement to sacrifice having larger amounts of HPs for the big time nukes. To put us as equals limits our class in thought when we are completely different and are supposed to be the masters of burst damage.<br><br>Yes the skill is given at 59, but as stated a lvl 59 is not going to stop to get this ability when regular xp is much more important. You must try to meet the wants of the overall community. A big bang nuke is what we ask for, not one with a cap that limits our damage to pretty pointless hits. I agree to leave the timer on when another MB can hit, though it should be lowered if not a tad. <br><br>finally i saw that an idea is to start off the ability at a gimp level and give more AAs to increase its power. I think thats unfair and uncaring of the developers against us when we have to work for those extra abilities. We spent our points in this ability for our big band, then it was nerfed, and when a promise to fix it was made many people bought it again. I feel to do that is to smack us in the face and treat us like an abused puppy.  If this is followed, i expect a chance to get our AAs back because i sure will want them.	
		</td></tr>
