			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=3222#M3222">87</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 549 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I can't really give quality feedback from the perspective of a level 59 wizard in pre-luclin content.  I'm a near end-game 70 wizard in current content.  Nonetheless, I'll try to give my perspective.<br><br>[quote]1) Leave manaburn pretty much as it is.  It keeps the 1 minute between casts and the long recast time.  Damage ratio stays the same with the damage done based solely on the amount of mana that is spent.  We'd add the ability for manaburn to crit so if the initial ability is capped at around 3k mana, the max damage would be 14k.  Advanced forms would use more mana so crit for significantly more.[/quote]<br><br>I can crit for over 14k with an ordinary nuke that costs 600ish.  Unless the scale of the upgrades for higher levels is pretty extraordinary, this would be an ability that I would use LESS than Manaburn in its current form.  Perhaps Manaburn should take into account focus effects similar to the way in which HT does?  That would provide some scaling with gear as well as additional levels of AA.  I don't mind the one minute timer as a limiter for certain encounters and to prevent farming abuse.<br> <br>[quote]2) Change manaburn so that it does 1 damage for every mana in your pool at the time it is cast, but doesn't actually use up any mana.  We'd add the ability for manaburn to crit so if the initial ability is capped at around 3k mana, the max damage would be 6k. Advanced forms would use more mana so crit for more.[/quote]<br><br>This is an interesting idea and one that I would use consistently, but only as additional mana-free dps, similar to the clicky nuke items.  Assuming that later AA allowed the ability to completely max out, I would be hitting for a normal hit of a little over 10k in ideal circumstance, which is a bit lower than a normal crit nuke.  With a crit, I'd land for more than I could currently achieve, which would be worthwhile, but only if Manaburn retained the current aggro characteristics, otherwise the combination of needing max mana to get the best effect and dealing with the aggro result would render it worthless.<br><br>[quote]For either of these changes, we'd also change manaburn from no-resist to a large negative resist to prevent the abuse of NPCs that are meant to be immune to spells.[/quote]<br><br>I have to say that I think this a HORRIBLE idea.  The no-resist portion of Manaburn is the ONLY reason that I have ever used the ability (I purchased it since the nerf).  There are plenty of fights where wizards just aren't useful without being able to land a no-resist spell and this change alone would be a large nerf for those encounters.<br><br>I'm not sure that I really grasp the purpose of this nerf or the fixes to it.  SK HT is still in original form and with AA works much like Manaburn did pre-nerf.  I haven't seen a big balancing issue with HT nor a lot of abuse.  I'd love to see a Manaburn fix, but so far the ideas I'm hearing sound more like further nerfs to an already lousy ability.  Manaburn used to be very powerful and it was balanced with the lack of other powerful class AA for wizards.  Other wizard class AAs include Quick Evacuation, which is completely superfluous with the addition of Exodus, which is shared with druids.  Quick Damage is a minor dps upgrade.  Improved Familiar has since seen upgrades.  Nexus Gate is silly.  Spell Casting Fury Mastery has been handed out to other classes as well.  Strong Root pales in comparison to shammy and druid root AAs.  Mana Burn was what defined wizards in class-specific AA.  We were already balanced around it.  Limiting the scale to prevent abuse of 4-5 year old content, if needed at all, shouldn't cripple the ability.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
