<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=3226#M3226">89</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 546 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>First let me say thanks for listening, sorry for ranting, but you asked for it... <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have been playing a wizard as my main for 6 years. Since Sept of 99' and in that time I have seen a lot of this game, and seen a lot of nerfs. Some warranted, others a little less so. However, I agree with fellow wizards here. Why bother to fix something if its not going to be 'worth' anything? If we can already crit for more or equal to the proposed manaburn fixes, then whats the point? Manaburn was supposed to take all our mana, leave us deffenseless, but do a massive amount of damage. I can already do 50K+ (on a bad day with tons of resists)&nbsp;in damage with a full mana bar, whats the difference? So what if it takes a little longer, and has a tad more risk, if any. The proposed fixes are NOT manaburn, they are a free low level nuke.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You keep saying SK / Nec harmtouch / lifeburn scale a little less then our manaburn. Yet, they can stack, and use them more often, then we can. Most of us don't even bother to use manaburn anymore, cause its worthless. SK's and Necro's can solo most of the mobs we could Manaburn back in the day. &nbsp;We are getting out damaged by rogues, monk, rangers, Mages, and necros. Hell even warriors now put out as much if not more then we do.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only way I see to fix manaburn, is to leave it the way it was back when it was released in Luclin. It&nbsp;based depending on our manapool. 1:2.5 No recast timer, no cap, no nothing. If this isn't doable, then don't do it at all, as anything else is a waste of AA's and the Developers time. Save your money SOE, we don't want another 'nerf' we want the origional thing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our class' sole purpose is big massive amounts of damage in a short time. We trade off Hitpoints, AC, and become a grape so we can pour burst damage out. Manaburn in its origional form was less 'efficent' then nuking, but it "helped kill that mob in an emergency". So what if there are MB Teams. As stated before warriors can now solo, what Manaburn teams killed. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am also curious as to why you all keep saying your going to keep it tuned to a level 59, as thats where we get the ability. As others have stated, what other AA's&nbsp;can't be used passed&nbsp;59?&nbsp;What level 59 wizard would spend 6AA's in General, 12 AA's in advanced, and 5 AA's in Class to get Manaburn, before getting say level 65? 2.5 years ago I might understand, but not today. In this lovely game of EQ, levels are probably the most important thing. They determine your resist check, AC, and so on. A level 59 wizard is going to get resisted more then a 65 wizard. Therefore said 59 wizard would most likely level up, not stop and get 23 AA's.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am also bothered that you say its too powerful in its origional use. Well, Team lifeburn could do the same thing if they wanted too, but why bother, when they can also solo the same mob, where a wizard can not. Necros, Sk's and Shamans all got their DoT cast times reduced in half. Why? cause mobs were dying too fast in groups that their dots were useless. Well, guess what, most wizards are lucky if they can get off more then 2 fast nukes in the same period.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I hope I have not offended anyone, but I think its a bit ridiculious to say the origional manaburn was 'overpowered'. It did less damage then our full manabar of nuking could do, but did it in a big burst.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sage Atom Smashur</DIV>
<DIV>Officer of the House of Requiem</DIV>
<DIV>The Tribunal Server (down with Aro!)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
