		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Gnomish Greetings!<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Rashere wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I've been working on changes to manaburn and wanted to get the wizard community feedback before proceeding.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>On the class re-envisionment statements, we said that our preferred method was to cap the damage based on a % of the npc's hit points, but I'm not fond of&nbsp;how that removes the ability to burn down an extra add in an emergency so wanted to present&nbsp;a couple other alternatives that we've been kicking around.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The core concept behind both of these is to&nbsp;remove the damage cap and instead cap the amount of mana you&nbsp;can spend.&nbsp; Advanced forms of the ability could then be introduced that offer more damage for higher level characters.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Leave manaburn pretty much as it is.&nbsp; It keeps the 1 minute between casts and the long recast time.&nbsp; Damage ratio stays the same with the damage done based solely on the amount of mana that is spent.&nbsp; We'd add the ability for manaburn to crit so if the initial ability is capped at around 3k mana, the max damage would be 14k.&nbsp; Advanced forms would use more mana so crit for significantly more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Change manaburn so that it does 1 damage for every mana in your pool at the time it is cast, but doesn't actually use up any mana.&nbsp; We'd add the ability for manaburn to crit so if the initial ability is capped at around 3k mana, the max damage would be 6k. Advanced forms would use more mana so crit for more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><U>For either of these changes, we'd also change manaburn from no-resist to a large negative resist to prevent the abuse of NPCs that are meant to be immune to spells.</U></STRONG>&nbsp; I'd also likely reduce the casting time significantly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Rashere</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>Not only are both options sucky, they are going to nerf it again. If it is resistable it means that dragons that are belly cast can't be nuke at full range to stay out of AE. It may be a small percentage of mobs, but it is still taking away from an already very limited ability. <BR><BR><STRONG><FONT size=4>EQLive is biased against wizards.</FONT></STRONG><BR>1) Option 1 keeps the recast delay not imposed on other class abilites.<BR>2) Option 2 is still capped when Lifeburn is not.<BR><BR>You all do what you want, I am not playing anymore.<!-- / message --><!-- sig --><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=2>Happy Birthday Wizard top 10 List!</FONT></STRONG><span></span><br><DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3><A href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=26846" target=_blank>Manaburn Manifesto on Graffe</A></FONT></STRONG><span></span>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
