<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=3245#M3245">100</a> of 352
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 446 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>While I think a more scalable version on Manaburn (i.e. later AAs to improve it) is a good idea, I don't understand why the Devs have such concerns over the stacking issue.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Say you have&nbsp;6 L70 wizards with maxxed MB, 10K mana each. Further assume for the sake of argument that max MB is going to be 30K, or 60K max crit. Whate exactly are they going to kill that they might want with 360K max 'instant' damage that might be an issue? Kunark mobs? Soloable by most classes. Velious? Also soloable. Luclin? 360K won't scratch most named there, and soloable by some anyway. GoD nameds? Either groupable, or 360K won't dent them. Same with PoP. Can't think of anything in OoW that 360K would kill except groupable nameds either. If some specific mobs or events are an issue, why not just flag them immune to Manaburn? If the Devs gave a specific example it might help us understand why this is a concern.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I rather liked the original proposal for re-implementing MB (preferably without the stacking issue). MB with a <EM>good</EM> (like 3:1 or better) but capped at %age of mobs total hp - if you think it might actually be used to burn down adds then make the %age cap scalable to the mob (if that's actually doable). That way when the raid leader says 'How much dps can you give me on the last 30% of this mob', maybe the wizards could actually do something useful instead of saying 'err, well, you should be asking the rogues really' .</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I also don't think the fact Manaburn was <EM>originally</EM> L59 is much of an issue. When L60 was the cap, you'd be getting the AAs because there was no more exp to get. Nowadayas, you're not going to stop at L59 to get 24AAs for Manaburn and then all your crit AAs as well. Also, I rather suspect the people who are still playing EQ the most these days are all over L59 <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>.</DIV>
